$EEENF Lets do some math and lets try to see how much 88E is worth as a worse case scenario.  
1. There's a 10% chance of prospective oil becoming commercial oil.  
2. Development costs for Alaska oil is  approx $35 per barrel.  
3. Prospective oil for 88 is 1.624BBO at 2P. 
4. Lets take cost of oil at an avg $65 for next 10 years.  
This gives: 
1,624,000,000*PofCommercialization*1/3(oil-dev cost)*2P/OS 
So putting the numbers in 
1,624,000,000*0.1*1/3(65-40)*0.5/14,000,000,000 = 0.077 
 
So at a minimum 88E is worth $0.08.
